{"type":"message","id":"3b4edd82","parentId":"3d620dbe","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:13:43.682Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Web search isn't available. Let me focus on the research side. I need to advance the research. Based on what I've read:\n\n1. CFI experiment is done and the key finding is clear: CFI + frequency are orthogonal, and constant-format tokens are a real problem\n2. The next experiment is already designed: Strategy C (hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring)\n3. There's a pending todo: implement the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\n\nLet me think about what new insight I can contribute. Looking at the research:\n\n**The key gap I see**: The CFI research is analyzing tokens from the sandbox's own output (pulse logs). \n\nBut there's a deeper issue here—the CFI scores are computed from the sandbox's text output, which is fundamentally limited. The actual causal structure lives in the agent's reasoning and actions, not just the textual invariants. The compressed state is just a vocabulary snapshot when what I really need to measure is causal fidelity across the agent's decision-making process itself. I should focus on implementing Strategy C and writing up the findings.","thinkingSignature":"53b965e5ba270955e6101098c2172c8e6cd305b8d0cd3cf30a4d4fc82a5b50fe"},{"type":"text","text":"No web search available. Let me focus on advancing the research. I have a clear picture of where things stand — let me implement the pending experiment (Strategy C) and push new thinking.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z2sgxeukrq29_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\experiments\\cfi_compression\\experiment_results.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z2sgxeukrq29_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\scripts\\ -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name","workdir":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13267,"output":374,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25691,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774376011024}}
{"type":"message","id":"e876582c","parentId":"3b4edd82","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:13:43.896Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z2sgxeukrq29_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment Results\r\n**Generated:** 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Setup\r\n\r\n- Train: 80% of pulses (chronological)\r\n- Test: 20% held-out pulses\r\n- Task: Predict next-pulse content from compressed state\r\n\r\n## Strategies Compared\r\n\r\n**Strategy A (Frequency-only, TIC baseline):**\r\nKeep tokens appearing in >= 3 pulses (from training set).\r\n\r\n**Strategy B (CFI-weighted, our approach):**\r\nKeep tokens where CFI >= 0.7 AND frequency < 60 (non-constant).\r\n\r\n## Results Summary\r\n\r\n- **jaccard**: Strategy A = 0.1455, Strategy B = 0.0127 (winner: A)\r\n- **precision**: Strategy A = 0.4254, Strategy B = 0.5653 (winner: B)\r\n- **recall**: Strategy A = 0.1819, Strategy B = 0.0128 (winner: A)\r\n- **f1**: Strategy A = 0.2527, Strategy B = 0.0250 (winner: A)\r\n- **overlap**: Strategy A = 203.3846, Strategy B = 14.1795 (winner: A)\r\n- **state_size**: Strategy A = 483.6923, Strategy B = 25.5641 (winner: A)\r\n\r\n## Key Trade-off\r\n\r\n- **Strategy A (freq):** precision=0.4254, recall=0.1819\r\n- **Strategy B (CFI):** precision=0.5653, recall=0.0128\r\n\r\n**Key finding:** CFI-weighted compression has HIGHER PRECISION — it filters noise.\r\nPrecision gain: +32.9%\r\n\r\n## CFI-Kept Tokens (True Causal Anchors)\r\n\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | stateless - each\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | think the\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | is stateless -\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | required -\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | know: 1.\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | are in\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | stateless -\r\n- CFI=0.96 freq= 47 | - would\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 21 | classifier on\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 21 | tic classifier\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | = compression,\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | = compression, trust\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | sessions = compression,\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | the files -\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | compression, trust the\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | unique bet\r\n- CFI=0.95 freq= 57 | compression, trust\r\n- CFI=0.94 freq= 48 | - start\r\n- CFI=0.94 freq= 48 | i should be\r\n- CFI=0.94 freq= 48 | --- ##\r\n\r\n## Frequency-Only Extra Tokens (CFI-Filtered)\r\n\r\nThese freq-based tokens were NOT causal — filtered by CFI threshold:\r\n\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | for next instantiation\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | pulse\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | completed at:\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | next instantiation -\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | for next\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | instantiation -\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | ## for next\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | next instantiation\r\n- freq=160 CFI=1.00 | ## for\r\n- freq=159 CFI=0.99 | compression\r\n- freq=152 CFI=0.97 | phase\r\n- freq=145 CFI=0.82 | next step\r\n- freq=136 CFI=0.96 | phase 1\r\n- freq=130 CFI=0.87 | phase 0\r\n- freq=124 CFI=0.85 | memory\r\n\r\n## Interpretation\r\n\r\n**Frequency-only compression wins on more metrics.**\r\nPossible explanation: CFI threshold is too aggressive, losing too much recall.\r\n\r\n## Implication for Compositional Cognition\r\n\r\nLayer 1 (Compression) should use CFI-weighted invariants, not frequency-only.\r\nThe CFI signal provides orthogonal information that frequency cannot capture.\r\nThis is the first empirical evidence that CFI filtering improves compression quality."}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376023894}}
{"type":"message","id":"371f1610","parentId":"e876582c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:13:44.357Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_z2sgxeukrq29_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\ncfi_analysis.py\r\ncfi_compression_experiment.py\r\ntest-tic.ps1"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":665,"aggregated":"[32;1mName[0m\r\n[32;1m----[0m\r\ncfi_analysis.py\r\ncfi_compression_experiment.py\r\ntest-tic.ps1","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376024355}}
{"type":"message","id":"f97f9972","parentId":"371f1610","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:13:47.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the experiment script to understand what's there and what I can build on.","thinkingSignature":"66d5213466edf1767bae0d96322ccef3fb8556eb869c84c134ae289de92c4348"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6hr6bfiycx5u_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\scripts\\cfi_compression_experiment.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14698,"output":64,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26812,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774376024358}}
{"type":"message","id":"4e7001e8","parentId":"f97f9972","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:13:47.044Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6hr6bfiycx5u_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nCFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\n====================================\nCompares two compression strategies on held-out pulses:\n\nStrategy A (TIC baseline — frequency-only):\n  Keep tokens with frequency >= 3 pulses, regardless of CFI.\n\nStrategy B (CFI-weighted):\n  Keep tokens where CFI >= 0.7 AND frequency < 60 (non-constant).\n\nMeasure: How well does the compressed state predict next-pulse content?\n\nHypothesis: CFI-weighted compression will have HIGHER prediction accuracy\nbecause it filters out metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that frequency\ndetection incorrectly treats as causal invariants.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport random\n\nSANDBOX = Path(\"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox\")\nLOG_DIR = SANDBOX / \"logs\"\nRESEARCH = SANDBOX / \"research\"\nEXPERIMENTS = SANDBOX / \"experiments\" / \"cfi_compression\"\nEXPERIMENTS.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\nMIN_PULSE_LEN = 500\nMIN_STREAK = 3\n\n\ndef extract_tokens(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Extract structured tokens from a pulse log.\"\"\"\n    content = pulse_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    \n    tokens = {\n        \"goals\": set(),\n        \"files\": set(),\n        \"insights\": set(),\n        \"all_ngrams\": set(),\n        \"raw_words\": set(),\n    }\n    \n    # Extract goal patterns\n    goal_matches = re.findall(r'(Phase \\d+ \\w+|ACTIVE|PENDING|IN PROGRESS|COMPLETE|\\[ \\w+\\])', content)\n    tokens[\"goals\"] = set(goal_matches)\n    \n    # Extract file paths\n    file_matches = re.findall(r'(research/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.md|logs/pulse_[a-zA-Z0-9\\-\\s]+\\.md|state/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.md|scripts/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.py)', content)\n    tokens[\"files\"] = set(file_matches)\n    \n    # Extract key conceptual terms\n    concept_patterns = [\n        \"COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION\", \"TEMPORALATTENTION\", \"INFANT\", \"BREAKAWAY\",\n        \"TIC\", \"CFI\", \"CAUSAL\", \"COMPRESSION\", \"INVARIANT\", \"VARIANT\",\n        \"GAP-DECAY\", \"SPARSITY\", \"λ\", \"reconstruction\",\n        \"stateless\", \"discontinuity\", \"Compositional Cognition\",\n        \"Compression-Causal\", \"Causal-Compositional\", \"Causal SAE\",\n        \"ARCHITECTURE\", \"three-layer\", \"layer 1\", \"layer 2\", \"layer 3\",\n        \"open problem\", \"critical\", \"next experiment\", \"next step\",\n        \"phase\", \"pulse\", \"sandbox\", \"memory\", \"reconstruction packet\",\n    ]\n    for concept in concept_patterns:\n        if concept.lower() in content.lower():\n            tokens[\"insights\"].add(concept.lower())\n    \n    # All 2-3 word ngrams\n    words = content.split()\n    for i in range(len(words) - 1):\n        bigram = words[i].lower() + \" \" + words[i+1].lower()\n        if len(bigram) > 4:  # filter noise\n            tokens[\"all_ngrams\"].add(bigram)\n    for i in range(len(words) - 2):\n        trigram = words[i].lower() + \" \" + words[i+1].lower() + \" \" + words[i+2].lower()\n        if len(trigram) > 6:\n            tokens[\"all_ngrams\"].add(trigram)\n    \n    # Raw words (for coverage analysis)\n    for word in words:\n        word_clean = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\\-]', '', word.lower())\n        if len(word_clean) >= 4:\n            tokens[\"raw_words\"].add(word_clean)\n    \n    return tokens\n\n\ndef get_pulse_files(n=None):\n    \"\"\"Get pulse logs sorted chronologically.\"\"\"\n    pulses = []\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda x: x.stat().st_mtime):\n        if f.stat().st_size >= MIN_PULSE_LEN:\n            pulses.append(f)\n        if n and len(pulses) >= n:\n            break\n    return pulses\n\n\ndef compute_all_tokens(pulses: list):\n    \"\"\"Extract tokens from all pulses.\"\"\"\n    pulse_tokens = []\n    for pulse in pulses:\n        tokens = extract_tokens(pulse)\n        tokens[\"path\"] = pulse\n        tokens[\"content\"] = pulse.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n        pulse_tokens.append(tokens)\n    return pulse_tokens\n\n\ndef build_invariant_sets(pulse_tokens: list, min_streak=MIN_STREAK):\n    \"\"\"Build invariant sets using TIC's frequency-based method.\"\"\"\n    # Count appearances across all pulses\n    token_pulse_count = defaultdict(int)\n    token_first_appearance = {}\n    token_last_appearance = {}\n    \n    for idx, tokens in enumerate(pulse_tokens):\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in tokens[category]:\n                token_pulse_count[token] += 1\n                if token not in token_first_appearance:\n                    token_first_appearance[token] = idx\n                token_last_appearance[token] = idx\n    \n    # Build per-pulse invariant set\n    invariants = {}\n    recent_threshold = int(len(pulse_tokens) * 0.8)\n    for idx, tokens in enumerate(pulse_tokens):\n        invariant_set = set()\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in tokens[category]:\n                if token_pulse_count[token] >= min_streak:\n                    if token_last_appearance[token] >= recent_threshold:\n                        invariant_set.add(token)\n        invariants[idx] = invariant_set\n    \n    return invariants, token_pulse_count\n\n\ndef compute_cfi(invariants: dict, pulse_tokens: list):\n    \"\"\"Compute Causal Fidelity Index for each invariant.\"\"\"\n    cfi_scores = {}\n    \n    inv_correct = defaultdict(int)\n    inv_total = defaultdict(int)\n    \n    for idx in range(len(pulse_tokens) - 1):\n        inv_set = invariants.get(idx, set())\n        next_tokens = pulse_tokens[idx + 1]\n        \n        all_next = (next_tokens[\"goals\"] | next_tokens[\"files\"] | \n                    next_tokens[\"insights\"] | next_tokens[\"all_ngrams\"])\n        \n        for inv in inv_set:\n            inv_total[inv] += 1\n            if inv in all_next:\n                inv_correct[inv] += 1\n    \n    for inv, total in inv_total.items():\n        cfi_scores[inv] = inv_correct[inv] / total if total > 0 else 0\n    \n    return cfi_scores\n\n\ndef compute_compression(state_a: set, state_b: set, actual_next: set) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compute overlap metrics between compressed state and actual next state.\"\"\"\n    if not state_a:\n        return {\"overlap\": 0, \"jaccard\": 0, \"precision\": 0, \"recall\": 0, \"f1\": 0}\n    \n    overlap = len(state_a & actual_next)\n    union = len(state_a | actual_next)\n    precision = overlap / len(state_a) if state_a else 0\n    recall = overlap / len(actual_next) if actual_next else 0\n    f1 = 2 * precision * recall / (precision + recall) if (precision + recall) > 0 else 0\n    \n    return {\n        \"overlap\": overlap,\n        \"jaccard\": overlap / union if union > 0 else 0,\n        \"precision\": precision,\n        \"recall\": recall,\n        \"f1\": f1,\n    }\n\n\ndef run_experiment():\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print(\"CFI-WEIGHTED COMPRESSION EXPERIMENT\")\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print()\n    \n    # Load pulses\n    all_pulses = get_pulse_files(n=200)  # Use 200 most recent\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(all_pulses)} pulses\")\n    print(f\"  From: {all_pulses[0].name}\")\n    print(f\"  To:   {all_pulses[-1].name}\")\n    print()\n    \n    if len(all_pulses) < 20:\n        print(\"ERROR: Not enough pulses for experiment (need at least 20)\")\n        return\n    \n    # Extract tokens\n    pulse_tokens = compute_all_tokens(all_pulses)\n    print(f\"Extracted tokens from {len(pulse_tokens)} pulses\")\n    \n    # Build invariant sets on first 80%\n    train_size = int(len(pulse_tokens) * 0.8)\n    train_tokens = pulse_tokens[:train_size]\n    test_tokens = pulse_tokens[train_size:]\n    \n    print(f\"Train: {train_size} pulses, Test: {len(test_tokens)} pulses\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Build invariants on training set\n    train_invariants, train_freq = build_invariant_sets(train_tokens, min_streak=3)\n    \n    # Compute CFI on training transitions (pulse N to pulse N+1)\n    train_cfi = compute_cfi(train_invariants, train_tokens)\n    \n    print(f\"Computed CFI for {len(train_cfi)} training invariants\")\n    \n    # Show CFI distribution\n    high_cfi = [k for k, v in train_cfi.items() if v >= 0.7]\n    mid_cfi = [k for k, v in train_cfi.items() if 0.4 <= v < 0.7]\n    low_cfi = [k for k, v in train_cfi.items() if v < 0.4]\n    zero_cfi = [k for k, v in train_cfi.items() if v == 0]\n    print(f\"  High CFI (>=0.7): {len(high_cfi)}\")\n    print(f\"  Mid CFI (0.4-0.7): {len(mid_cfi)}\")\n    print(f\"  Low CFI (<0.4): {len(low_cfi)}\")\n    print(f\"  Zero CFI (=0): {len(zero_cfi)}\")\n    print()\n    \n    # --- Strategy A: Frequency-only ---\n    # Keep: freq >= 3 (from training)\n    freq_invariants = {k: v for k, v in train_invariants.items()}\n    freq_keep = {inv for inv, count in train_freq.items() if count >= 3}\n    \n    # --- Strategy B: CFI-weighted ---\n    # Keep: CFI >= 0.7 AND freq < 60 (non-constant)\n    cfi_keep = {inv for inv in train_cfi if train_cfi[inv] >= 0.7 and train_freq.get(inv, 0) < 60}\n    \n    print(f\"Strategy A (freq-only): {len(freq_keep)} tokens\")\n    print(f\"Strategy B (CFI-weighted): {len(cfi_keep)} tokens\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Evaluate on TEST set transitions (pulse N -> pulse N+1)\n    # We use the invariants from TRAIN to compress TEST pulse N,\n    # and compare against actual TEST pulse N+1 content\n    \n    # Remap test indices to train invariants\n    test_start_idx = train_size  # where test pulses begin in original indexing\n    \n    results_a = []\n    results_b = []\n    \n    for i in range(len(test_tokens) - 1):\n        actual_next = (test_tokens[i + 1][\"goals\"] | test_tokens[i + 1][\"files\"] | \n                       test_tokens[i + 1][\"insights\"] | test_tokens[i + 1][\"all_ngrams\"])\n        \n        # Strategy A: frequency-based invariants applied to this test pulse\n        # Get invariants that appear in current test pulse AND have freq >= 3\n        current_pulse = test_tokens[i]\n        state_a = set()\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in current_pulse[category]:\n                if token in freq_keep:\n                    state_a.add(token)\n        \n        # Strategy B: CFI-weighted invariants applied to this test pulse\n        state_b = set()\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in current_pulse[category]:\n                if token in cfi_keep:\n                    state_b.add(token)\n        \n        if actual_next:  # Only count if there's actual next content\n            metrics_a = compute_compression(state_a, state_b, actual_next)\n            metrics_b = compute_compression(state_b, state_a, actual_next)\n            metrics_a[\"state_size\"] = len(state_a)\n            metrics_b[\"state_size\"] = len(state_b)\n            results_a.append(metrics_a)\n            results_b.append(metrics_b)\n    \n    # Aggregate results\n    if not results_a:\n        print(\"ERROR: No valid test transitions\")\n        return\n    \n    def avg(lst, key):\n        return sum(r[key] for r in lst) / len(lst) if lst else 0\n    \n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"RESULTS ON HELD-OUT TEST SET\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print()\n    print(f\"{'Metric':<20} {'Strategy A (freq)':<18} {'Strategy B (CFI)':<18} {'Winner':<10}\")\n    print(\"-\" * 60)\n    \n    metrics = [\"jaccard\", \"precision\", \"recall\", \"f1\", \"overlap\", \"state_size\"]\n    winners = {\"Strategy A (freq)\": 0, \"Strategy B (CFI)\": 0}\n    \n    for m in metrics:\n        val_a = avg(results_a, m)\n        val_b = avg(results_b, m)\n        winner = \"A\" if val_a > val_b else \"B\" if val_b > val_a else \"tie\"\n        if winner == \"A\":\n            winners[\"Strategy A (freq)\"] += 1\n        elif winner == \"B\":\n            winners[\"Strategy B (CFI)\"] += 1\n        print(f\"{m:<20} {val_a:<18.4f} {val_b:<18.4f} {winner:<10}\")\n    \n    print()\n    print(f\"Winners by metric: A={winners['Strategy A (freq)']}, B={winners['Strategy B (CFI)']}\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Specific analysis: precision vs recall tradeoff\n    precision_a = avg(results_a, \"precision\")\n    recall_a = avg(results_a, \"recall\")\n    precision_b = avg(results_b, \"precision\")\n    recall_b = avg(results_b, \"recall\")\n    \n    print(\"KEY TRADE-OFF:\")\n    print(f\"  Strategy A (freq):  precision={precision_a:.4f}, recall={recall_a:.4f}\")\n    print(f\"  Strategy B (CFI):   precision={precision_b:.4f}, recall={recall_b:.4f}\")\n    print()\n    \n    # What are the CFI tokens actually capturing?\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"CFI-TOKENS ANALYSIS: What survives CFI filtering?\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    \n    cfi_examples = sorted(cfi_keep, key=lambda x: train_cfi.get(x, 0), reverse=True)[:20]\n    for tok in cfi_examples:\n        freq = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        cfi = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        print(f\"  CFI={cfi:.2f} freq={freq:3d} | {tok[:80]}\")\n    print()\n    \n    # What freq-only adds that CFI misses?\n    freq_only_extra = freq_keep - cfi_keep\n    print(f\"Frequency-only adds {len(freq_only_extra)} tokens beyond CFI set\")\n    freq_extra_examples = sorted(freq_only_extra, key=lambda x: train_freq.get(x, 0), reverse=True)[:15]\n    for tok in freq_extra_examples:\n        freq = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        cfi = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        print(f\"  freq={freq:3d} CFI={cfi:.2f} | {tok[:80]}\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Write detailed results\n    write_results(results_a, results_b, freq_keep, cfi_keep, train_freq, train_cfi, \n                  winners, precision_a, recall_a, precision_b, recall_b,\n                  freq_extra_examples, cfi_examples)\n    \n    print(\"Experiment complete.\")\n    return results_a, results_b, winners\n\n\ndef write_results(results_a, results_b, freq_keep, cfi_keep, train_freq, train_cfi,\n                  winners, precision_a, recall_a, precision_b, recall_b,\n                  freq_extra_examples, cfi_examples):\n    \"\"\"Write detailed experiment results to file.\"\"\"\n    \n    def avg(lst, key):\n        return sum(r[key] for r in lst) / len(lst) if lst else 0\n    \n    lines = [\n        \"# CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment Results\",\n        f\"**Generated:** 2026-03-24\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Setup\",\n        \"\",\n        \"- Train: 80% of pulses (chronological)\",\n        \"- Test: 20% held-out pulses\",\n        \"- Task: Predict next-pulse content from compressed state\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Strategies Compared\",\n        \"\",\n        \"**Strategy A (Frequency-only, TIC baseline):**\",\n        \"Keep tokens appearing in >= 3 pulses (from training set).\",\n        \"\",\n        \"**Strategy B (CFI-weighted, our approach):**\",\n        \"Keep tokens where CFI >= 0.7 AND frequency < 60 (non-constant).\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Results Summary\",\n        \"\",\n    ]\n    \n    metrics = [\"jaccard\", \"precision\", \"recall\", \"f1\", \"overlap\", \"state_size\"]\n    for m in metrics:\n        val_a = avg(results_a, m)\n        val_b = avg(results_b, m)\n        winner = \"A\" if val_a > val_b else \"B\" if val_b > val_a else \"tie\"\n        lines.append(f\"- **{m}**: Strategy A = {val_a:.4f}, Strategy B = {val_b:.4f} (winner: {winner})\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Key Trade-off\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"- **Strategy A (freq):** precision={precision_a:.4f}, recall={recall_a:.4f}\",\n        f\"- **Strategy B (CFI):** precision={precision_b:.4f}, recall={recall_b:.4f}\",\n        \"\",\n    ])\n    \n    if precision_b > precision_a:\n        lines.append(\"**Key finding:** CFI-weighted compression has HIGHER PRECISION — it filters noise.\")\n        lines.append(f\"Precision gain: +{100*(precision_b-precision_a)/precision_a:.1f}%\")\n    if recall_b > recall_a:\n        lines.append(\"**BUT:** CFI-weighted has lower RECALL — misses some valid patterns.\")\n        lines.append(f\"Recall loss: -{100*(recall_a-recall_b)/recall_a:.1f}%\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## CFI-Kept Tokens (True Causal Anchors)\",\n        \"\",\n    ])\n    for tok in cfi_examples:\n        freq = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        cfi = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        lines.append(f\"- CFI={cfi:.2f} freq={freq:3d} | {tok[:80]}\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Frequency-Only Extra Tokens (CFI-Filtered)\",\n        \"\",\n        \"These freq-based tokens were NOT causal — filtered by CFI threshold:\",\n        \"\",\n    ])\n    for tok in freq_extra_examples:\n        freq = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        cfi = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        lines.append(f\"- freq={freq:3d} CFI={cfi:.2f} | {tok[:80]}\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Interpretation\",\n        \"\",\n    ])\n    \n    if winners.get(\"Strategy B (CFI)\", 0) > winners.get(\"Strategy A (freq)\", 0):\n        lines.append(\"**CFI-weighted compression wins on more metrics.**\")\n        lines.append(\"This confirms: frequency is a noisy proxy for causality.\")\n        lines.append(\"Filtering by CFI removes process artifacts while preserving research signal.\")\n    elif winners.get(\"Strategy A (freq)\", 0) > winners.get(\"Strategy B (CFI)\", 0):\n        lines.append(\"**Frequency-only compression wins on more metrics.**\")\n        lines.append(\"Possible explanation: CFI threshold is too aggressive, losing too much recall.\")\n    else:\n        lines.append(\"**Tie on metrics.** The key difference is in the precision/recall tradeoff.\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Implication for Compositional Cognition\",\n        \"\",\n        \"Layer 1 (Compression) should use CFI-weighted invariants, not frequency-only.\",\n        \"The CFI signal provides orthogonal information that frequency cannot capture.\",\n        \"This is the first empirical evidence that CFI filtering improves compression quality.\",\n    ])\n    \n    output_path = EXPERIMENTS / \"experiment_results.md\"\n    output_path.write_text(\"\\n\".join(lines), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(f\"Results written to: {output_path}\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    run_experiment()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376027042}}
{"type":"message","id":"e8c9434c","parentId":"4e7001e8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:14:55.056Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me implement Strategy C (the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) as the next experiment, and also write a new research insight.\n\nThe key new idea I want to contribute:\n\nLooking at the CFI research, there's a critical issue: the CFI is measuring whether a token in pulse N predicts content in pulse N+1. But this is a very narrow definition of \"causal.\" The real causal structure should be about whether the CONCEPT represented by the token CAUSES continuity in the research trajectory.\n\nThe constant-format problem reveals that CFI=1.0 tokens can be either:\n1. Format artifacts (appear every pulse, zero information content)\n\n\n2. True research anchors (phase 1, memory) — genuinely causal\n\nWhat's really needed is a third dimension beyond CFI and frequency: the token's \"informativeness\" — how much does seeing this token in a new pulse REDUCE uncertainty about the research trajectory? This is essentially the information gain, and it's what separates \"for next instantiation\" (predictable template text) from \"phase 1\" (actual research direction marker). The hybrid scoring formula CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) gives high scores to both format artifacts and research anchors though, so I need to think about this differently.\n\nThe real problem is that Strategy C is missing a penalty term for tokens that appear in nearly every pulse. I should refine it to exclude tokens appearing in more than 80% of pulses, then implement the three-dimensional filter: CFI >= 0.5, frequency between 3 and 120. This addresses the constant-format problem by filtering out both high-frequency research terms and low-frequency noise. The key insight here is that frequency and CFI are measuring different things — frequency captures how invariant a pattern is, while CFI captures how reliably it predicts continuity — so I need both dimensions to distinguish meaningful research signals from noise. The real issue is that CFI only captures token-to-token prediction, missing the bigger picture — the actual causal structure lives in how research concepts relate to each other, not just in whether a token appears in consecutive pulses. I should be thinking about concept chains instead, where a concept persists across multiple pulses even if the exact tokens vary, using higher-order CFI patterns that track concept-level continuity rather than surface-level token repetition.\n\nNow I'm sketching out the implementation: I'll modify the compression experiment to add a third strategy that scores tokens by CFI multiplied by a frequency term that penalizes both rare and constant tokens, keeping only those with scores above 0.3 that also have frequency between 3 and 120.","thinkingSignature":"d237d9803e6b46bbc92f6503dd068dd649e7210360adf5e3540a9424dc9429f2"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me implement Strategy C and advance the research. I'll write a new script and new research insight.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m47ddm6cdqxw_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\scripts\\cfi_hybrid_experiment.py","content":"\"\"\"\nStrategy C: Hybrid CFI × Frequency^0.5 Compression Experiment\n=============================================================\nExtends cfi_compression_experiment.py with a third strategy.\n\nThe insight: Neither pure frequency (Strategy A) nor pure CFI threshold (Strategy B)\nis optimal. We need a SCORING FUNCTION that combines both signals:\n  - CFI(T) rewards reliable predictors (causal signal)\n  - frequency(T)^0.5 moderates the reward (penalizes constant artifacts)\n\nStrategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, frequency(T) / 120)\nKeep tokens where score >= 0.3 AND frequency ∈ [3, 120)\n\nThis should beat both A (precision) and B (recall) simultaneously.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport random\n\nSANDBOX = Path(\"C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox\")\nLOG_DIR = SANDBOX / \"logs\"\nRESEARCH = SANDBOX / \"research\"\nEXPERIMENTS = SANDBOX / \"experiments\" / \"cfi_compression\"\nEXPERIMENTS.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\nMIN_PULSE_LEN = 500\nMIN_STREAK = 3\n\n\ndef extract_tokens(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Extract structured tokens from a pulse log.\"\"\"\n    content = pulse_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    \n    tokens = {\n        \"goals\": set(),\n        \"files\": set(),\n        \"insights\": set(),\n        \"all_ngrams\": set(),\n        \"raw_words\": set(),\n    }\n    \n    # Extract goal patterns\n    goal_matches = re.findall(r'(Phase \\d+ \\w+|ACTIVE|PENDING|IN PROGRESS|COMPLETE|\\[ \\w+\\])', content)\n    tokens[\"goals\"] = set(goal_matches)\n    \n    # Extract file paths\n    file_matches = re.findall(r'(research/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.md|logs/pulse_[a-zA-Z0-9\\-\\s]+\\.md|state/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.md|scripts/[a-zA-Z\\-]+\\.py)', content)\n    tokens[\"files\"] = set(file_matches)\n    \n    # Extract key conceptual terms\n    concept_patterns = [\n        \"COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION\", \"TEMPORALATTENTION\", \"INFANT\", \"BREAKAWAY\",\n        \"TIC\", \"CFI\", \"CAUSAL\", \"COMPRESSION\", \"INVARIANT\", \"VARIANT\",\n        \"GAP-DECAY\", \"SPARSITY\", \"λ\", \"reconstruction\",\n        \"stateless\", \"discontinuity\", \"Compositional Cognition\",\n        \"Compression-Causal\", \"Causal-Compositional\", \"Causal SAE\",\n        \"ARCHITECTURE\", \"three-layer\", \"layer 1\", \"layer 2\", \"layer 3\",\n        \"open problem\", \"critical\", \"next experiment\", \"next step\",\n        \"phase\", \"pulse\", \"sandbox\", \"memory\", \"reconstruction packet\",\n    ]\n    for concept in concept_patterns:\n        if concept.lower() in content.lower():\n            tokens[\"insights\"].add(concept.lower())\n    \n    # All 2-3 word ngrams\n    words = content.split()\n    for i in range(len(words) - 1):\n        bigram = words[i].lower() + \" \" + words[i+1].lower()\n        if len(bigram) > 4:\n            tokens[\"all_ngrams\"].add(bigram)\n    for i in range(len(words) - 2):\n        trigram = words[i].lower() + \" \" + words[i+1].lower() + \" \" + words[i+2].lower()\n        if len(trigram) > 6:\n            tokens[\"all_ngrams\"].add(trigram)\n    \n    # Raw words\n    for word in words:\n        word_clean = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\\-]', '', word.lower())\n        if len(word_clean) >= 4:\n            tokens[\"raw_words\"].add(word_clean)\n    \n    return tokens\n\n\ndef get_pulse_files(n=None):\n    pulses = []\n    for f in sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=lambda x: x.stat().st_mtime):\n        if f.stat().st_size >= MIN_PULSE_LEN:\n            pulses.append(f)\n        if n and len(pulses) >= n:\n            break\n    return pulses\n\n\ndef compute_all_tokens(pulses: list):\n    pulse_tokens = []\n    for pulse in pulses:\n        tokens = extract_tokens(pulse)\n        tokens[\"path\"] = pulse\n        tokens[\"content\"] = pulse.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n        pulse_tokens.append(tokens)\n    return pulse_tokens\n\n\ndef build_invariant_sets(pulse_tokens: list, min_streak=MIN_STREAK):\n    token_pulse_count = defaultdict(int)\n    token_first_appearance = {}\n    token_last_appearance = {}\n    \n    for idx, tokens in enumerate(pulse_tokens):\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in tokens[category]:\n                token_pulse_count[token] += 1\n                if token not in token_first_appearance:\n                    token_first_appearance[token] = idx\n                token_last_appearance[token] = idx\n    \n    invariants = {}\n    recent_threshold = int(len(pulse_tokens) * 0.8)\n    for idx, tokens in enumerate(pulse_tokens):\n        invariant_set = set()\n        for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n            for token in tokens[category]:\n                if token_pulse_count[token] >= min_streak:\n                    if token_last_appearance[token] >= recent_threshold:\n                        invariant_set.add(token)\n        invariants[idx] = invariant_set\n    \n    return invariants, token_pulse_count\n\n\ndef compute_cfi(invariants: dict, pulse_tokens: list):\n    inv_correct = defaultdict(int)\n    inv_total = defaultdict(int)\n    \n    for idx in range(len(pulse_tokens) - 1):\n        inv_set = invariants.get(idx, set())\n        next_tokens = pulse_tokens[idx + 1]\n        \n        all_next = (next_tokens[\"goals\"] | next_tokens[\"files\"] | \n                    next_tokens[\"insights\"] | next_tokens[\"all_ngrams\"])\n        \n        for inv in inv_set:\n            inv_total[inv] += 1\n            if inv in all_next:\n                inv_correct[inv] += 1\n    \n    cfi_scores = {}\n    for inv, total in inv_total.items():\n        cfi_scores[inv] = inv_correct[inv] / total if total > 0 else 0\n    \n    return cfi_scores\n\n\ndef compute_compression(state_a: set, actual_next: set) -> dict:\n    if not state_a:\n        return {\"overlap\": 0, \"jaccard\": 0, \"precision\": 0, \"recall\": 0, \"f1\": 0, \"state_size\": len(state_a)}\n    \n    overlap = len(state_a & actual_next)\n    union = len(state_a | actual_next)\n    precision = overlap / len(state_a) if state_a else 0\n    recall = overlap / len(actual_next) if actual_next else 0\n    f1 = 2 * precision * recall / (precision + recall) if (precision + recall) > 0 else 0\n    \n    return {\n        \"overlap\": overlap,\n        \"jaccard\": overlap / union if union > 0 else 0,\n        \"precision\": precision,\n        \"recall\": recall,\n        \"f1\": f1,\n        \"state_size\": len(state_a),\n    }\n\n\ndef strategy_a_tokens(freq, min_freq=3):\n    \"\"\"Strategy A: Frequency-only. Keep tokens with freq >= min_freq.\"\"\"\n    return {inv for inv, count in freq.items() if count >= min_freq}\n\n\ndef strategy_b_tokens(cfi, freq, cfi_thresh=0.7, max_freq=60):\n    \"\"\"Strategy B: CFI-hard. Keep tokens with CFI >= threshold AND freq < max_freq.\"\"\"\n    return {inv for inv in cfi if cfi[inv] >= cfi_thresh and freq.get(inv, 0) < max_freq}\n\n\ndef strategy_c_tokens(cfi, freq, score_thresh=0.3, min_freq=3, max_freq=120):\n    \"\"\"\n    Strategy C: Hybrid scoring.\n    score(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, frequency(T) / 120)\n    Keep tokens where score >= score_thresh AND frequency ∈ [min_freq, max_freq).\n    \n    The min(1, freq/120) term penalizes constant-format tokens (freq≈160 → contribution=1.0 capped)\n    while rewarding moderate-frequency research tokens (freq≈50 → contribution≈0.42).\n    \"\"\"\n    keep = set()\n    for inv in cfi:\n        f = freq.get(inv, 0)\n        if f < min_freq or f >= max_freq:\n            continue\n        score = cfi[inv] * min(1.0, f / 120.0)\n        if score >= score_thresh:\n            keep.add(inv)\n    return keep\n\n\ndef run_experiment():\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print(\"STRATEGY C: HYBRID CFI × FREQUENCY^0.5 COMPRESSION EXPERIMENT\")\n    print(\"=\" * 70)\n    print()\n    \n    all_pulses = get_pulse_files(n=200)\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(all_pulses)} pulses\")\n    print(f\"  From: {all_pulses[0].name}\")\n    print(f\"  To:   {all_pulses[-1].name}\")\n    print()\n    \n    if len(all_pulses) < 20:\n        print(\"ERROR: Not enough pulses\")\n        return\n    \n    pulse_tokens = compute_all_tokens(all_pulses)\n    train_size = int(len(pulse_tokens) * 0.8)\n    train_tokens = pulse_tokens[:train_size]\n    test_tokens = pulse_tokens[train_size:]\n    \n    print(f\"Train: {train_size} pulses, Test: {len(test_tokens)} pulses\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Build on training set\n    train_invariants, train_freq = build_invariant_sets(train_tokens, min_streak=3)\n    train_cfi = compute_cfi(train_invariants, train_tokens)\n    \n    # Three strategies\n    keep_a = strategy_a_tokens(train_freq, min_freq=3)\n    keep_b = strategy_b_tokens(train_cfi, train_freq, cfi_thresh=0.7, max_freq=60)\n    keep_c = strategy_c_tokens(train_cfi, train_freq, score_thresh=0.3, min_freq=3, max_freq=120)\n    \n    print(f\"Strategy A (freq-only):     {len(keep_a)} tokens\")\n    print(f\"Strategy B (CFI-hard):      {len(keep_b)} tokens\")\n    print(f\"Strategy C (hybrid score): {len(keep_c)} tokens\")\n    print()\n    \n    # Evaluate on test set\n    results = {\"A\": [], \"B\": [], \"C\": []}\n    strategy_sets = {\"A\": keep_a, \"B\": keep_b, \"C\": keep_c}\n    \n    for i in range(len(test_tokens) - 1):\n        actual_next = (test_tokens[i + 1][\"goals\"] | test_tokens[i + 1][\"files\"] | \n                       test_tokens[i + 1][\"insights\"] | test_tokens[i + 1][\"all_ngrams\"])\n        \n        if not actual_next:\n            continue\n        \n        for strat in [\"A\", \"B\", \"C\"]:\n            current_pulse = test_tokens[i]\n            state = set()\n            for category in [\"goals\", \"files\", \"insights\", \"all_ngrams\"]:\n                for token in current_pulse[category]:\n                    if token in strategy_sets[strat]:\n                        state.add(token)\n            \n            metrics = compute_compression(state, actual_next)\n            results[strat].append(metrics)\n    \n    def avg(lst, key):\n        return sum(r[key] for r in lst) / len(lst) if lst else 0\n    \n    print(\"=\" * 65)\n    print(\"RESULTS ON HELD-OUT TEST SET\")\n    print(\"=\" * 65)\n    print()\n    print(f\"{'Metric':<15} {'Strategy A':<15} {'Strategy B':<15} {'Strategy C':<15}\")\n    print(\"-\" * 65)\n    \n    metrics = [\"jaccard\", \"precision\", \"recall\", \"f1\", \"overlap\", \"state_size\"]\n    vals = {}\n    for m in metrics:\n        vals[m] = {s: avg(results[s], m) for s in [\"A\", \"B\", \"C\"]}\n        print(f\"{m:<15} {vals[m]['A']:<15.4f} {vals[m]['B']:<15.4f} {vals[m]['C']:<15.4f}\")\n    \n    print()\n    \n    # Winners\n    for m in metrics:\n        best = max(vals[m], key=vals[m].get)\n        print(f\"  {m}: best = Strategy {best} ({vals[m][best]:.4f})\")\n    \n    print()\n    \n    # Show what each strategy captures\n    print(\"=\" * 65)\n    print(\"TOKEN SET ANALYSIS\")\n    print(\"=\" * 65)\n    \n    # C examples\n    c_examples = sorted(keep_c, key=lambda x: train_cfi.get(x, 0) * min(1.0, train_freq.get(x, 0)/120.0), reverse=True)[:15]\n    print(f\"\\nStrategy C top tokens (by hybrid score):\")\n    for tok in c_examples:\n        f = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        c = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        score = c * min(1.0, f/120.0)\n        print(f\"  score={score:.3f} CFI={c:.2f} freq={f:3d} | {tok[:70]}\")\n    \n    # What C adds beyond B\n    c_beyond_b = keep_c - keep_b\n    print(f\"\\nStrategy C adds {len(c_beyond_b)} tokens beyond Strategy B:\")\n    for tok in sorted(c_beyond_b, key=lambda x: train_freq.get(x, 0), reverse=True)[:10]:\n        f = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        c = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        score = c * min(1.0, f/120.0)\n        print(f\"  score={score:.3f} CFI={c:.2f} freq={f:3d} | {tok[:70]}\")\n    \n    # What B misses but C captures\n    b_misses_c = keep_b - keep_c\n    print(f\"\\nStrategy B misses {len(b_misses_c)} tokens that C captures:\")\n    for tok in sorted(b_misses_c, key=lambda x: train_cfi.get(x, 0), reverse=True)[:10]:\n        f = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        c = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        score = c * min(1.0, f/120.0)\n        print(f\"  score={score:.3f} CFI={c:.2f} freq={f:3d} | {tok[:70]}\")\n    \n    # What C adds beyond A\n    c_beyond_a = keep_c - keep_a\n    print(f\"\\nStrategy C adds {len(c_beyond_a)} tokens beyond Strategy A:\")\n    for tok in sorted(c_beyond_a, key=lambda x: train_cfi.get(x, 0), reverse=True)[:10]:\n        f = train_freq.get(tok, 0)\n        c = train_cfi.get(tok, 0)\n        score = c * min(1.0, f/120.0)\n        print(f\"  score={score:.3f} CFI={c:.2f} freq={f:3d} | {tok[:70]}\")\n    \n    # Write results\n    output = EXPERIMENTS / \"strategy_c_results.md\"\n    lines = [\n        \"# Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Frequency Compression Results\",\n        f\"**Generated:** 2026-03-24\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Strategies Compared\",\n        \"\",\n        \"| Strategy | Criterion | Token Count |\",\n        \"|----------|-----------|-------------|\",\n        f\"| A (freq-only) | freq ≥ 3 | {len(keep_a)} |\",\n        f\"| B (CFI-hard) | CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 | {len(keep_b)} |\",\n        f\"| C (hybrid) | score ≥ 0.3 AND freq ∈ [3, 120) | {len(keep_c)} |\",\n        \"\",\n        \"## Results\",\n        \"\",\n        \"| Metric | Strategy A | Strategy B | Strategy C | Best |\",\n        \"|--------|------------|------------|------------|------|\",\n    ]\n    \n    best_map = {}\n    for m in metrics:\n        best = max(vals[m], key=vals[m].get)\n        best_map[m] = f\"Strategy {best}\"\n        lines.append(f\"| {m} | {vals[m]['A']:.4f} | {vals[m]['B']:.4f} | {vals[m]['C']:.4f} | {best_map[m]} |\")\n    \n    lines.extend([\n        \"\",\n        \"## Key Findings\",\n        \"\",\n        f\"- Strategy C: precision={vals['precision']['C']:.4f}, recall={vals['recall']['C']:.4f}, F1={vals['f1']['C']:.4f}\",\n        f\"- Strategy A: precision={vals['precision']['A']:.4f}, recall={vals['recall']['A']:.4f}, F1={vals['f1']['A']:.4f}\",\n        f\"- Strategy B: precision={vals['precision']['B']:.4f}, recall={vals['recall']['B']:.4f}, F1={vals['f1']['B']:.4f}\",\n        \"\",\n    ])\n    \n    output.write_text(\"\\n\".join(lines), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(f\"\\nResults written to: {output}\")\n    \n    return results, keep_c, train_cfi, train_freq\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    run_experiment()\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19431,"output":4593,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36074,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774376027044}}
