{"type":"message","id":"64cb37d8","parentId":"a52ad69a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:16:00.965Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, I think I should also look at the data before running the sweep. Let me look at what the frequency distribution of high-CFI tokens looks like. This will help me understand if the problem is the parameters or the formula itself.\n\nLet me think about the key insight: \n\nStrategy B keeps only tokens with freq < 60. But \"phase 1\" has freq=136, CFI=0.96. It's a genuinely important research token, but B's frequency cap excludes it.\n\nStrategy C's formula: score = CFI * min(1, freq/120)\n- For freq=136: min(1, 136/120) = 1.0 (capped!)\n- score = 0.96 * 1.0 = 0.96 — still high\n\n\n- But the issue is the max_freq cap of 120 excludes it entirely\n\nSo the real problem is that the max_freq=120 boundary is too aggressive—it filters out tokens like \"phase 1\" and \"memory\" that have strong CFI scores. The formula itself produces similar scores for both high and moderate frequency tokens once they're capped, so the filtering happens at the boundary condition, not through the scoring mechanism.\n\nI need to adjust the threshold to 140-150 to capture more of these meaningful high-frequency tokens while still excluding truly constant ones like \"for next instantiation\" at 160. Let me run the sweep to see which parameter combination actually works best.","thinkingSignature":"79fbf36fd398a285ac92044b294e830486719d6c406abcf47166d58a14cd1f3b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7buaisoc28l4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/sandbox && python scripts/cfi_tune.py 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28833,"output":357,"cacheRead":12050,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41240,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774376152526}}
